Task 6: Data Persistence with Docker Volumes

Implementation:
Containers are ephemeral by nature (data is lost when the container is deleted). 
To solve this, I implemented Docker Volumes.

Created a Volume: 
'''bash
docker volume create my_volume

Mounted the Volume: 
Ran the container with the -v flag to map the host volume to the container path.
Bash
docker run -d -p 8080:80 -v my_volume:/app/data <your-username>/sample-app:v1.0

Why use Volumes?
Data Persistence: Critical for databases or log files; data survives container restarts and deletions.

Decoupling: Separates the application code (image) from the data (volume).

Portability: Volumes can be easily backed up or migrated between containers.
